"{\"abstract\":\"Existing approaches to causal embeddings rely heavily on hand-crafted high-precision causal patterns, leading to limited coverage. To solve this problem, this paper proposes a method to boost causal embeddings by exploring potential verbmediated causal patterns. It first constructs a seed set of causal word pairs, then uses them as supervision to characterize the causal strengths of extracted verb-mediated patterns, and finally exploits the weighted extractions by those verb-mediated patterns in the construction of boosted causal embeddings. Experimental results have shown that the boosted causal embeddings outperform several state-of-the-arts significantly on both English and Chinese. As by-products, the top-ranked patterns coincide with human intuition about causality.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"92775630\",\"name\":\"Zhipeng Xie\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/92775630\"},{\"authorId\":\"65979463\",\"name\":\"Feiteng Mu\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/65979463\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":199466451,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2019/266\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"9daf34d6aa916c8f8d36abfbf9c83877490d862a\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"70066534\",\"name\":\"Ralph A. Szweda\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\",\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"73308d733f603e5ebf86c782499e6e06bad4a42e\",\"title\":\"Information processing management\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/73308d733f603e5ebf86c782499e6e06bad4a42e\",\"venue\":\"\",\"year\":1972},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1719404\",\"name\":\"Alessandro Moschitti\"},{\"authorId\":\"144865351\",\"name\":\"Bo Pang\"},{\"authorId\":\"1735272\",\"name\":\"W. Daelemans\"}],\"doi\":\"10.3115/v1/d14-1\",\"intent\":[\"backgrou